10: Okay, okay! I'll get up and make it—
20:
It's four o'clock in the morning. Why
the hell are you cooking?!
30:
With minced meat and onions. You
fry them together in a pan. I like to
add dried shiitake mushrooms for
flavor.
31:
You can make it more kid-friendly
by mixing in a bit of sugar and milk
in there too, she'll love it—
34: "She"? What am I even talking about?
50: "Huh"? Is that all you have to say?
54:
O-oh... I'm sorry, I don't remember
anything... What happened?
58:
You were frying eggs like your life
depended on it, and then you went
and collapsed on the floor. That's
what happened.
65:
That's putting it mildly. Think it could
be something you ate?
68:
I dunno about that... If anything, I
wish that was the case.
72:
For a moment there, I felt like I could
remember... Anyway, I'm sorry about
all that.
76:
You know, I just got some serious
déjà vu of the time you got stabbed.
88:
Well that's certainly one way to
greet the guy who just saved your
ass.
95:
Sorry about that. I guess I still get
spooked easily...
97:
But more importantly—thank you for
saving me.
101:
Now why'd you have to go and do
something reckless like that, huh?
104:
You usually hang in the back, away
from the action. Why the hell did you
decide to throw caution to the wind
THIS time around?
107:
Nimbus, tell me... What do you think
of Light and Stella?
111:
Huh? Why?
...I guess I'd say the two of them are
pretty nuts. Stella especially.
115:
Exactly... Stella always jumps right in,
doesn't she?
118:
She doesn't even think about getting
hurt or anything—she just
immediately goes for it, guns
blazing.
124:
Sorry to break it to you, but getting
stabbed doesn't make you crazy all
of a sudden. Unless you also hit your
head or somethin'.
131:
But that doesn't change the fact
that I want to be more like her.
135:
"I wanna do more dangerous stuff,"
said the guy who just got stabbed in
the abdomen. Give me a break, Alk.
140:
Yeah... You're right, Nimbus. I'm
sorry...
144:
Sheesh. Seriously though, no more
of this risky business, all right? You
do it again, I'll be super pissed.
147:
I'll be more careful next time. Sorry,
Nimbus...
149:
I appreciate it. You worrying about
me and all.
153:
Yeah, yeah. Don't get all sentimental
on me now.
160:
Oh... So you're saying I did the same
thing again? I got myself in trouble
by being reckless...
163:
Mhm. That would be what I'm sayin',
yep.
167:
You know... I've been having more
and more dreams lately. Ever since
we fought Procheon.
170:
Dreams of your past? Hmm. You
said you didn't care about stuff like
that before.
173:
I think it was more that I was afraid
of knowing the truth. But now things
are different. Now I need to know the
truth.
176:
Finding out more about your past
self helped you out, didn't it? It made
you a stronger person.
190:
Are you okay? Are you alive? Are you
in pain? Can you move?
194:
I-I'm fine, Stella! Really! I didn't get
stabbed this time around. It was just
a small case of exhaustion from
overworking.
202:
Now that you've figured out the
problem, it's time to fix it. Get some
sleep. Getting restless and
overdoing it never helped anybody.
210:
I guess you can leave the
housework to me in the meantime.
That's what I'm here for, after all—to
clean up your mess.
216:
...Oh gosh, should we really be
leaving the chores to Nimbus?! I
better recover fast...
224:
Oh, that's a great idea... That would
put my mind at ease for sure.
228:
I'm sorry, Stella, I really need to get
some sleep.
